1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,739
The 25th Amendment

2
00:00:01,740 --> 00:00:02,739
Section 1

3
00:00:02,740 --> 00:00:04,799
In case of the removal of the President

4
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:07,539
from office or of his death or resignation,

5
00:00:07,540 --> 00:00:09,839
the Vice President shall become President.

6
00:00:09,840 --> 00:00:11,079
Section 2

7
00:00:11,080 --> 00:00:12,669
Whenever there is a vacancy

8
00:00:12,670 --> 00:00:14,299
in the office of the Vice President,

9
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:16,809
the President shall nominate a Vice President

10
00:00:16,810 --> 00:00:19,139
who shall take office upon confirmation

11
00:00:19,140 --> 00:00:22,009
by a majority vote of both Houses of Congress.

12
00:00:22,010 --> 00:00:23,149
Section 3

13
00:00:23,150 --> 00:00:24,889
Whenever the President transmits

14
00:00:24,890 --> 00:00:26,999
to the President pro tempore of the Senate

15
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,309
and the Speaker of the House of Representatives

16
00:00:29,310 --> 00:00:31,869
his written declaration that he is unable

17
00:00:31,870 --> 00:00:34,469
to discharge the powers and duties of his office,

18
00:00:34,470 --> 00:00:36,069
and until he transmits to them

19
00:00:36,070 --> 00:00:38,229
a written declaration to the contrary,

20
00:00:38,230 --> 00:00:40,599
such powers and duties shall be discharged

21
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:43,289
by the Vice President as Acting President.

22
00:00:43,290 --> 00:00:44,489
Section 4

23
00:00:44,490 --> 00:00:47,249
Whenever the Vice President and a majority of either

24
00:00:47,250 --> 00:00:49,859
the principal officers of the executive departments

25
00:00:49,860 --> 00:00:53,359
or of such other body as Congress may by law provide,

26
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:56,199
transmit to the President pro tempore of the Senate

27
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:58,389
and the Speaker of the House of Representatives

28
00:00:58,390 --> 00:01:00,399
their written declaration that the President

29
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:03,939
is unable to discharge the powers and duties of his office,

30
00:01:03,940 --> 00:01:06,289
the Vice President shall immediately assume

31
00:01:06,290 --> 00:01:09,499
the powers and duties of the office as Acting President.

32
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:11,569
Thereafter, when the President transmits

33
00:01:11,570 --> 00:01:13,749
to the President pro tempore of the Senate

34
00:01:13,750 --> 00:01:15,949
and the Speaker of the House of Representatives

35
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:19,139
his written declaration that no inability exists,

36
00:01:19,140 --> 00:01:21,949
he shall resume the powers and duties of his office

37
00:01:21,950 --> 00:01:24,199
unless the Vice President and a majority

38
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:27,169
of either the principal officers of the executive department

39
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:30,239
or of such other body as Congress may by law provide,

40
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:31,749
transmit within four days

41
00:01:31,750 --> 00:01:33,949
to the President pro tempore of the Senate

42
00:01:33,950 --> 00:01:36,109
and the Speaker of the House of Representatives

43
00:01:36,110 --> 00:01:38,699
their written declaration that the President is

44
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:41,939
unable to discharge the powers and duties of his office.

45
00:01:41,940 --> 00:01:44,519
Thereupon Congress shall decide the issue,

46
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:46,469
assembling within forty-eight hours

47
00:01:46,470 --> 00:01:48,569
for that purpose if not in session.

48
00:01:48,570 --> 00:01:50,529
If the Congress, within twenty-one days

49
00:01:50,530 --> 00:01:52,949
after receipt of the latter written declaration,

50
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:55,099
or, if Congress is not in session,

51
00:01:55,100 --> 00:01:58,609
within twenty-one days after Congress is required to assemble,

52
00:01:58,610 --> 00:02:01,369
determines by two-thirds vote of both Houses

53
00:02:01,370 --> 00:02:03,059
that the President is unable

54
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:05,669
to discharge the powers and duties of his office,

55
00:02:05,670 --> 00:02:07,309
the Vice President shall continue

56
00:02:07,310 --> 00:02:09,879
to discharge the same as Acting President;

57
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:11,989
otherwise, the President shall resume

58
00:02:11,990 --> 00:02:14,220
the powers and duties of his office.

